<paragraph id="E46436E7FFBC0D67FF36D47AB0FFF7C1" blockId="4.[136,1452,1089,2088]" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">
Notes:—In the phylogenetic analysis, 
<taxonomicName id="23DB4D64FFBC0D67FDE5D479B7E4F9C6" authorityName="Phutthacharoen &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2021" box="[622,998,1557,1583]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Ploettnerulaceae" genus="Rhexocercosporidium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="18" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="camporesii">
<emphasis id="D6AFEAF5FFBC0D67FDE5D479B7E4F9C6" box="[622,998,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">Rhexocercosporidium camporesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clustered sister to 
<taxonomicName id="23DB4D64FFBC0D67FB5CD47AB1A9F9C6" box="[1239,1451,1557,1583]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Helotiaceae" genus="Pirottaea" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="18" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="brevipila">
<emphasis id="D6AFEAF5FFBC0D67FB5CD47AB1A9F9C6" box="[1239,1451,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">Pirottaea brevipila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(CBS 309.58) with high support in BI analysis (0.99 BYPP), but low support in ML and MP analyses (50% ML, 34% MP). Unfortunately, the 
<taxonomicName id="23DB4D64FFBC0D67FE52D432B65CF99E" box="[473,606,1629,1656]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Helotiaceae" genus="Pirottaea" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="18" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="brevipila">
<emphasis id="D6AFEAF5FFBC0D67FE52D432B5E8F99E" box="[473,490,1630,1655]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D6AFEAF5FFBC0D67FE71D431B65CF99E" box="[506,606,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">brevipila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
strain does not link to any type material or morphological description (
<bibRefCitation id="804A4B16FFBC0D67FA02D432B50BF975" author="Vu, D. &amp; Groenewald, M. &amp; De Vries, M. &amp; Gehrmann, T. &amp; Stielow, B. &amp; Eberhardt, U. &amp; Al-Hatmi, A. &amp; Groenewald, J. Z. &amp; Cardinali, G. &amp; Houbraken, J. &amp; Boekhout, T. &amp; Crous, P. W. &amp; Robert, V. &amp; Verkler, G. J. M." pageId="4" pageNumber="18" pagination="135 - 154" refId="ref6924" refString="Vu, D., Groenewald, M., De Vries, M., Gehrmann, T., Stielow, B., Eberhardt, U., Al-Hatmi, A., Groenewald, J. Z., Cardinali, G., Houbraken, J., Boekhout, T., Crous, P. W., Robert, V. &amp; Verkler, G. J. M. (2019) Large-scale generation and analysis of filamentous fungal DNA barcodes boosts coverage for kingdom fungi and reveals thresholds for fungal species and higher taxon delimitation. Studies in Mycology 92: 135 - 154. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. simyco. 2018.05.001" type="journal article" year="2019">
Vu 
<emphasis id="D6AFEAF5FFBC0D67FF03D4EEB4BEF972" box="[136,188,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
). However, the illustrations of the 
<typeStatus id="3B608845FFBC0D67FD17D4EDB6FCF972" box="[668,766,1665,1691]" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="23DB4D64FFBC0D67FCA3D4EEB7ACF972" box="[808,942,1665,1692]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Helotiaceae" genus="Pirottaea" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="18" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="brevipila">
<emphasis id="D6AFEAF5FFBC0D67FCA3D4EEB73BF972" box="[808,825,1666,1691]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D6AFEAF5FFBC0D67FCC1D4EDB7ACF972" box="[842,942,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">brevipila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows black hair surrounding the apothecia and the species lacks an amyloid ring (
<bibRefCitation id="804A4B16FFBC0D67FDCAD4C9B6F1F929" author="Schroeter, J." box="[577,755,1701,1728]" pageId="4" pageNumber="18" refId="ref6475" refString="Schroeter, J. (1889) Die Pilze Schlesiens. J. U. Kern's Verlag, Breslau, 597 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 45927" type="book" year="1889">Schroeter 1889</bibRefCitation>
). In contrast, 
<taxonomicName id="23DB4D64FFBC0D67FC04D4C9B104F956" authorityName="Phutthacharoen &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2021" box="[911,1286,1701,1727]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Ploettnerulaceae" genus="Rhexocercosporidium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="18" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="camporesii">
<emphasis id="D6AFEAF5FFBC0D67FC04D4C9B104F956" box="[911,1286,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">Rhexocercosporidium camporesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not have hair around the apothecia, and it has an amyloid ring. Morphology of our new species differed significantly from the other 
<taxonomicName id="23DB4D64FFBC0D67FF41D481B619F8EE" box="[202,539,1773,1799]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Ploettnerulaceae" genus="Rhexocercosporidium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="18" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="D6AFEAF5FFBC0D67FF41D481B5BDF8EE" box="[202,447,1773,1799]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">Rhexocercosporidium</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, and these differences are listed in 
<tableCitation id="A959035CFFBC0D67FC27D481B001F8E1" box="[940,1027,1773,1800]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="7.[136,224,966,990]" captionText="TABLE 2. Comparison of the morphological features of the sexual states of Rhexocercosporidium and Pirottaea brevipila." pageId="4" pageNumber="18">Table 2</tableCitation>
. However, we could not compare the morphology of our species with 
<taxonomicName id="23DB4D64FFBC0D67FE78D57EB665F8C2" box="[499,615,1810,1836]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Ploettnerulaceae" genus="Rhexocercosporidium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="18" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="carotae">
<emphasis id="D6AFEAF5FFBC0D67FE78D57EB606F8C2" box="[499,516,1810,1835]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D6AFEAF5FFBC0D67FD99D57EB665F8C2" box="[530,615,1810,1835]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">carotae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(CBS 418.65) as this species was introduced with only an asexual morph. To further support the establishment of the new taxon, we compared nucleotide differences in both LSU and ITS gene regions (
<bibRefCitation id="804A4B16FFBC0D67FF61D536B5EAF89D" author="Jeewon, R. &amp; Hyde, K. D." box="[234,488,1881,1908]" pageId="4" pageNumber="18" pagination="1669 - 1677" refId="ref5958" refString="Jeewon, R. &amp; Hyde, K. D. (2016) Establishing species boundaries and new taxa among fungi: recommendations to resolve taxonomic ambiguities. Mycosphere 7: 1669 - 1677. https: // doi. org / 10.5943 / mycosphere / 7 / 11 / 4" type="journal article" year="2016">Jeewon &amp; Hyde 2016</bibRefCitation>
). The nucleotide comparison between 
<taxonomicName id="23DB4D64FFBC0D67FC16D536B03AF89A" authorityName="Phutthacharoen &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2021" box="[925,1080,1882,1907]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Ploettnerulaceae" genus="Rhexocercosporidium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="18" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="camporesii">
<emphasis id="D6AFEAF5FFBC0D67FC16D536B03AF89A" box="[925,1080,1882,1907]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">R. camporesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="23DB4D64FFBC0D67FBFAD536B0E5F89A" box="[1137,1255,1882,1907]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Ploettnerulaceae" genus="Rhexocercosporidium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="18" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="carotae">
<emphasis id="D6AFEAF5FFBC0D67FBFAD536B0E5F89A" box="[1137,1255,1882,1907]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">R. carotae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MFLU 17-1594 and CBS 418.65), revealed 10/672 base pair differences (1.48%) in the LSU sequence and 26/560 base pairs (4.64%), including gaps in the ITS region. The difference between 
<taxonomicName id="23DB4D64FFBC0D67FC9DD5CEB7B3F852" authorityName="Phutthacharoen &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2021" box="[790,945,1954,1980]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Ploettnerulaceae" genus="Rhexocercosporidium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="18" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="camporesii">
<emphasis id="D6AFEAF5FFBC0D67FC9DD5CEB725F852" box="[790,807,1954,1979]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D6AFEAF5FFBC0D67FCBDD5CEB7B3F852" box="[822,945,1954,1979]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">camporesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MFLU 17-1594) and 
<taxonomicName id="23DB4D64FFBC0D67FB33D5CEB14FF852" authorityName="Phutthacharoen &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2020" box="[1208,1357,1954,1980]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Ploettnerulaceae" genus="Rhexocercosporidium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="18" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="senecionis">
<emphasis id="D6AFEAF5FFBC0D67FB33D5CEB0CBF852" box="[1208,1225,1954,1979]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D6AFEAF5FFBC0D67FB53D5CEB14FF852" box="[1240,1357,1954,1979]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">senecionis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MFLU 17-1635) was 5/853 base pair differences (0.58%) for LSU and 31/591 base pair differences (5.24%), including gaps for ITS. A comparison between 
<taxonomicName id="23DB4D64FFBC0D67FE7FD586B68DF7EA" authorityName="Phutthacharoen &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2021" box="[500,655,2026,2052]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Ploettnerulaceae" genus="Rhexocercosporidium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="18" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="camporesii">
<emphasis id="D6AFEAF5FFBC0D67FE7FD586B607F7EA" box="[500,517,2026,2051]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D6AFEAF5FFBC0D67FD9FD586B68DF7EA" box="[532,655,2026,2051]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">camporesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MFLU 17-1594) and 
<taxonomicName id="23DB4D64FFBC0D67FC1CD586B035F7EA" box="[919,1079,2026,2052]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Ploettnerulaceae" genus="Rhexocercosporidium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="18" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="microspora">
<emphasis id="D6AFEAF5FFBC0D67FC1CD586B7AAF7EA" box="[919,936,2026,2051]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D6AFEAF5FFBC0D67FC3CD586B035F7EA" box="[951,1079,2026,2051]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">microspora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MFLU 18-2672) showed 5/843 base pair differences for LSU and 51/598 base pair differences (8.52%) in ITS region, including gaps.
</paragraph>
